I agree with a previous poster, Martha Stewart has a fabulous carrot cake recipe. However, the request I received was for a "plain and traditional" carrot cake, so I thought that probably ruled out the fresh ginger, orange zest and candied carrot ribbons (although it's exactly what I'll be doing for my own birthday!). On the advice of other reviewers, I reduced the fat to one cup. I did not replace the extra fat with anything, and it turned out fine. I have no idea where an extra half cup of oil would have gone. If I made this again, I'd reduce the fat by a little more still. I found it on the bland side, so I would suggest adding more cinnamon, and maybe some ground ginger to the batter. All in all, I think "plain and traditional" fits this one well. I'll add it to my repertoire for a decent standby cake, but in my mind it's certainly not the over-the-top sort of dessert that other people described it as. IMHO

