This is a fantastic, moist cake that is not too light, nor too dense. It has a classic carrot cake crumb and is very flavourful. I made the following changes to the recipe as I like flavourful foods: 1 1/3 cups vegetable, rather than 1 1/2 cups; 4 jumbo eggs, rather than 4 large eggs; 1 3/4 teaspoons cinnamon, rather than 1 teaspoon; 1 teaspoon ground nutmeg, rather than 3/4 teaspoon; 1/4 teaspoon ground cloves; 1 cup raisins, rather than 1/2 cup. I divided the batter between two 9 inch square pans and baked for 45 minutes. I filled and frosted it with a lemon cream cheese frosting, which provided a really nice contrast to the carrot cake spice. Yum!

