This cake is always a hit with people. I've made it many times with the following alterations. 1) Decrease oil to 1 cup 2) Add 1/2 cup of applesauce OR 8oz can crushed pineapple 3) Decrease sugar to 1 1/2 cup 4) Increase nuts and (golden)raisins to 1 cup each 5) I dump all the ingredients into one bowl and mix them with a wooden spoon at the same time -- easier, faster, and is works perfectly fine. The cake is moist without being oily and is not too sweet when you eat it with the frosty.

