Would give it 5 forks if that were an option!!! Substituted 1 cup applesauce with 1/4 cup oil in place of the 1.5 cups of oil stated in the recipe. Also used 1 cup of oat flour with 1 cup regular unbleached flour. I added an extra 3/4 cup chopped walnuts to the mix and doubled the spices. Lastly, inspired by an earlier reviewer, I soaked the raisins in Grand Marnier for about 5 hours prior to cooking. Also used some of the left over Grand Marnier in the frosting (but watch it, a little goes a loooong way in the frosting!). Used fresh lemon juice in the frosting to cut some of the sweetness. Cake was still moist and to-die-for 3 days later!!!

