Rating: 4
I made this cake vegan. I subbed the 4 eggs with ½ of a large banana, ¼ cup of vanilla soy yogurt, and 2 eggs worth of egg replacer. I also used a little less sugar, and used ½ brown sugar and ½ white sugar. The cake tasted really good and had some loft (less fluffy than non-vegan, of course) but could have had less sugar and was a little to oily. Next time, Ill try it with less oil and even less sugar. Maybe a total of 1.5 cups of sugar instead of 2 cups. Oh, I also chopped and slow roasted the pecans before adding them to the cake to deepen their flavor. Yum! For vegan frosting, I used 2 sticks of vegan butter and about 2 C of powdered sugar with some vanilla, and about ¼ C of coconut milk, and some dried coconut, and just a hint of salt. This made a really good vegan buttercream. It may have been even better if Id used ½ vegan butter and ½ vegan shortening. However, the buttery frosting wasnt perfect for the already oily cake. Next time Ill try a vegan fake cream cheese frosting. I shied away from that this time because vegan cheese is always weird.

