Rating: 4
There is a reason there are a zillion reviews for this cake. It's outstanding. I "grated" the carrots by shredding them in a FP first, then chopping the shreds with the FP using the metal blade. My variations: I subbed 1/2 cup melted butter for part of the oil. I used 1 full cup of ground walnuts and 1 full cup of ground craisins. Baked the recipe in a half-sheet pan for exactly 45 minutes. CC icing I used was 2 lbs. of softened CC with 1 cup of granulated sugar and 1 tsp. of vanilla. Beaten long enough, granulated sugar will dissolve. This cake is going into my keeper file. It's the moistest, most flavorful carrot cake I ever made.

