Rating: 3
This is very tasty and moist, but didn't come out with a standard cake texture. But here's what I did after I read some of the reviews: used a little less sugar, replaced over 3/4 c of oil with vanilla yogourt, grated the carrots extra fine for more moisture (my theory) and added orange peel to the icing. Wow that icing is good. I really whipped it, made it easy to spread. I could have waited just a wee bit longer for the cake to cool to make sure there was no melting from warm cake. A note for those who want some but not tons of icing, I only made half the icing recipe and baked the cake in just 2 layers and there was enough to cover. I might have added a wee bit more butter as I didn't measure, just put what I had left in. So I'll definitely try this again, maybe even follow the recipe more closely.

Rating: 0
Recipe turned out well. I greased the pans with butter and then lined them with parchment paper. I would not suggest wax paper, since the film could melt into your food. I omitted the raisins and nuts, since some folks don't care for them and b/c I don't think they're essential to a good carrot cake. I added about a quarter teaspoon of ginger, but don't think it really came through. I also used vanilla bean paste in the icing, which really enhanced the flavor. Also, I'd recommend spraying the cooling rack with Pam. I didn't and ended up with stuck cake. Whoops.

Rating: 4
This is exceptional and very easy to make. Made it for the first time for my husband's birthday - at my 8 yr old's insistence that we make a home- made cake. She was so thrilled to help and aside from me handling the carrot grating, I let her take the lead for most of the steps. Used as much organic ingredients as i could - flour, butter, eggs, sugar, carrots, applesauce. Followed some substitutions as per some of the reviews: For cake, I substituted 1 cup applesauce for the 1c veg oil. Put in remaining 1/2 c veg oil. Subbed 1/2 c crushed, drained pineapple for the raisins as no one in our family likes raisins in cakes. TOASTED the nuts first before I stirred in. Added 1/2 t vanilla. And really, really dont forget the wax paper to line the pan - I was almost going to skip because I had nonstick cake pans but I am so glad I didnt! You will be scrapping your carrot cake from pan if you dont put in the wax paper liner. Poured in 2 10-in pans to make 2 layers. For the frosting, followed another review and mixed 2 8oz cream cheese, 2 c powdered sugar, 2 t vanilla, 1 stick butter and either zest of orange or 2 t lemon juice. Its very easy to adjust up or down on the sugar depending how sweet you want it. Next time i will decrease the butter to 3/4 stick. Refrigerated frosting for 30-45 min before i put in on cake and had no problem of being runny. Wonderful! My husband LOVES carrot cake and he was oohing and aahing the whole time. This is a definite keeper.

