Rating: 4
I recently baked this cake for a family get together. I was pleasantly surprised when everyone said it was the "best carrot cake they'd ever had". I went ahead and reduced the oil to 3/4 cup and then substituted 3/4 cup of applesauce for the rest of the oil. I doubled the cinnamon and reduced the nutmeg to 1/4 tsp as I am not a big nutmeg fan. I also added a scant amount of ground cloves and 1/4 tsp vanilla extract. I left out the raisins (due to picky eaters) and chose to decorate the sides of the cake with the pecans. I baked the cake in 3, 8-inch foil pans at 325 and it only took 40 minutes in my oven. For the frosting, I took the advice of another reviewer (Page Mavis from NJ) and added the zest of one orange. (The frosting was so tasty that I couldn't stop eating it while I was frosting the cake!) I served the cake cold and found that with each passing day it became more and more delicious! It is true that this cake will win over people who claim to "hate" carrot cake. It is now a delicious addition to our family's cook book.

