This cake recipe is really, really good. I made the following modifications and it was still really excellent: substituted 8 oz (1 cup) of unsweetened applesauce for 1 cup of oil (still used the other 1/2 cup oil). Added a small can (about 1/2 cup) of crushed pineapple, drained. Doubled the cinnamon and eliminated the nutmeg because I just don't like the stuff. Also didn't add the nuts. The only thing that I didn't like was the original frosting recipe. Granted, I did use neufchatel, which can get a little gummy/runny when beaten, but I had to add at least two more cups of powdered sugar to get the flavor/consistency of frosting that I like. Though, I tend to like my frosting sweet. Overall, it was a great cake and I'd make it again. It's for my dad's birthday tomorrow (his request) and I think he'll be pleased.

