This has become my standard carrot cake. I've made it over and over, and have finally found that a few changes has produced the "best carrot cake ever" for a hard-to-impress crowd. I leave out the raisins as I've never liked them in carrot cake but also use the nuts only on the frosting and around the base of the cake because of a finicky son so he can pick them off. Works best if you reduce the oil to 1 1/4 cup (at most) and reduce the nutmeg - just a bit will do. Add a teaspoon of vanilla for richer flavor. Can bake as a double layer cake as well.

