Rating: 3
I'm sort of confounded by this recipe and the reviews. I followed the recipe exactly, wanting to try it as written. It produced three not-very-high layers which sunk pretty seriously in the middle. It was very oily (left serious oil marks on the cardboard cake round I placed it on). Following suggestions of reviewers re the frosting, I tried to use less sugar, but you really need at least 3 cups to make a proper frosting that's not just a sheer glaze (how the previous reviewer got by with 3/4 cup I can't figure out). The frosting barely covered the cake, and with the big, coarse, oily crumbs all over it was a bit difficult to frost at all. I persevered and put it in the fridge overnight to take to a work party. In the morning I added another layer of cream cheese frosting I had left over (w/orange peel, from a spice cake recipe on this site), and it looked more presentable, though far from attractive. Served it in the afternoon to about a dozen people, most of whom said it was the best carrot cake they'd ever had! It was certainly moist. I think all of the suggestions to cut the oil and sub w/applesauce are worth following, and I'm wondering if a full tablespoon of baking powder and soda might be indicated. The cake does taste better the second day. I'm not sure what to make of all this, but if ten people say it's out of this world they must be right, I guess!

