Made for Easter dessert and got rave reviews. Would have given 4 forks, but made these changes: Substituted 1/2 C applesauce instead of oil; increased cinnamon to 1 1/2 tsp; increased nutmeg to 1 tsp; added one 8 oz. can of crushed pineapple, drained; reduced powdered sugar (frosting) to 2 1/2 C; reduced vanilla (frosting) to 2 tsp; added 1 tsp lemon zest to frosting. I also omitted the nuts and raisins (personal preference). Decorated cake with pecans and refrigerated for easy cutting. Next time I'll increase to cinnamon and nutmeg slightly- otherwise, I'll make exactly the same. YUMMY!!!

