I followed the recommendations of prior cooks and substituted 1/2 cup of applesauce for a 1/2 cup of the oil; I'm certain that simple change improved the texture and taste of the resulting cake. This cake was moist with a nice crumb, not overly sweet, and left the pan very easily (lining the 9x13" pan with waxed paper did the trick). I love the flavor of vanilla, but, in my opinion, the 4 teaspoons of vanilla in the icing overpowered the milder carrot and spice flavors of the cake. I think 1 teaspoon of vanilla (a normal amount for most recipes) will yield better results the next time I bake this cake.

