Because of the modifications made by previous reviewers, this was a fantastic cake!! I made it twice this week and it was a hit both times. Here are my notes: -Definitely use the applesauce to replace some of the oil (1/2 c applesauce and 1c oil). -Definitely increase the carrot. I used 4 cups. -Definitely increase the spices. I added more cinnamon and some pumpkin pie spice. -I replaced 2 of the whole eggs with 2 egg whites only, and it was still moist and delicious. -I made it once with 2 nine-inch pans and once with 3 pans. It comes out fine either way, but I vastly preferred the 3-layer version. Better cake to icing ratio. -I used pastry flour once and all-purpose once, and it was pretty much the same either way. -I cut the sugar to 1 and a half cups in the icing and I thought it was perfect. Don't forget the vanilla!

