In the seventies I made a carrot cake that always won rave reviews. Unfortunately in one of my many moves I lost the recipe. I decided to try this one out, but I couldn't help tweaking it a bit. I replaced the two cups of sugar with one cup of brown sugar splenda. Reduced oil to one cup. Used one cup cake flour, one cup whole wheat. Ground the cinnamon and nutmeg fresh and switched proportions 3/4 t cinnamon to 1 t nutmeg, added a handful of wheatgerm and used six cups of carrots instead of three. I would have used currants instead of the raisins but I couldn't find any, so we skipped the raisins. Cake was wonderful. Not too dry, not too moist, not too dense, lovely nutty carroty perfume brought to life by the nutmeg. The icing was a disappointment. I think I would make it next time without the butter. It was too soft and too sweet. Of course my husband thought the icing made the cake!

