Rating: 4
I prepared this cake according to the suggestions below and it was excellent. I don't think it would be very good without the following changes, as it would be too sweet and oily: Substitue 1/2 cup applesauce for 1/2 c. oil (i.e., 1 cup oil and 1/2 cups applesauce). Sustitute 1/2 drained crushed pineapple for raisins. Reduce sugar in cake from 2 cups to 1 1/2 c. Reduce sugar in frosting to 2 cups. This edited recipe results in a dense moist cake with an interesting texture and a tangy perfectly sweet frosting.

