ABSOLUTELY INCREDIBLE. The recipe as written probably merits 3 forks but the variations given below bring it up to 4 forks (I've never given 4 forks to any recipe before). The variations I used were: replace 1/2 cup of oil for buttermilk, add a can of drained crushed pineapple and replaced pecans for walnuts. I also added a tablespoon more of flour as the batter looked too wet. I made it in a 9x13 pan and baked for 40 minutes. The frosting is another story. I made a half a batch and used only 1 cup of powdered sugar (amount of powdered sugar in frosting is definitely a typo). 4 tsp. of vanilla changed the color of the frosting and just didn't taste right so I added some lemon zest. Will try orange zest next time instead. I love carrot cake and this is by far the BEST I'VE EVER HAD. Received rave reviews from everyone lucky enough to get a piece before it was gobbled up. The cake is good enough to eat without frosting. Will try it as cupcakes (w/ frosting) or muffins (w/o) next time. TERRIFIC!

