Wow - what a fantastic cake! I made for Easter dessert and everyone raved. I followed the directions pretty much to the note, with the exception of cooking time. My cakes cooked in much less time than 45 minutes - so just keep an eye on them. Also - a hint.. I made two of these cakes, on the first I peeled the wax paper off of the layers as they were cooling and on the second I left the wax paper on until I was ready to frost. I think 2nd cake turned out better - more moist. All in all I thought this was a fantasic and simple recipe that I will definately make again. Oh - another tip - use raisins that are marked as "baking raisins" they are much juicier and hold up better in the baking process.

