After seeing all the rave reviews about this carrot cake, I couldn't wait to try it. What a huge disappointment! I was foolish enough to try it for the first time when we had company so I was not pleased! First of all, 45 min. is WAY too long to cook the layers. I left mine in for 45 min. like the recipe said, and they were way overcooked and even burnt on the edges. I made the icing exactly the way the recipe said and even though I refrigerated it for two hours before icing the cake, it was so runny. Last but not least, three 9" cake pans won't fit on one rack in the oven, when I closed the door, two of the pans got pushed together and so were not flat and the cakes turned out very uneven. Try icing a cake that has three uneven layers. Good grief, what a mess. The cake was so dry it was barely edible. A huge disappointment, BUT I will try it once more and try baking the layers for 22 minutes like one cook reccommended instead of the 45 the recipe calls for. I must say that I would think that these recipes should be tested more thoroughly before being posted so that everyone doesn't have to make so many changes to the recipe before it is a decent one.

