Rating: 3
For a really fresh tasting cream cheese frosting, take your standard recipe and substitute freshly grated lemon rind for any vanilla extract. After tasting it with the lemon rind, any cream cheese frosting made with vanilla will taste cloying to you. Here's my standard verison: 8 oz. cream cheese, 6 tbl. softened butter, 1 1/2 tsp. freshly grated lemon rind, and approx. 1 lb. of Confectioners sugar. If I don't like the consistency, I'll add more sugar to thicken or a little water to thin.

