Rating: 4
Let me begin by saying that I can't stand when people take good desert recipes and transform them into low-fat, tasteless ones. My motto is "if you are going to eat desert, eat desert!" However, since I was only making this for my husband and myself who are both on diets I decided to experiment and make a low-fat cake on a whim. I replaced all of the vegetable oil in the cake with applesauce and replaced the four eggs with five egg whites. For the frosting I replaced the cream cheese with 1/3 Less Fat Philedelphia Cream Cheese (Neufshatel?) and omitted the butter. I had to refrigerate the frosting a little to harden it some before using because it was a little runny. I watched eagerly as my critical, picky, and very skeptical carrot cake conniseur husband tasted it..."very good...very, very good...beautiful cake"! was his answer and I have to agree! It was very, very moist, easy to make, had all the great flavor of carrot cake AND was guilt free.

