Rating: 4
Re the frosting -it is essential not to overbeat - the more you do the thinner it gets & people add more icing to thicken it up which doesnt work & just makes it too sweet. I used butter rather than margarine as it sets harder obviously. Soften it & the cream cheese either by leaving it out or you could microwave it for a very short time but do not let it start to melt. Beat these together until just combined then lightly fold in your icing sugar (a little lemon juice is nice)- you dont need all the sugar the recipe says - taste as you go till it is right for you then refrigerate. Pure icing sugar will also set harder than icing mix.

