Rating: 4
I made this recipe for the first time today with much success. The cake turned out delicious & moist. You always know you have a winner when someone asks for the recipe. I had several requests. I did not use nutmeg but did use alittle more cinnamon & all spice, no raisins-8 oz. can of drained crushed pineapple instead. Used "fine pecan meal" (finely chopped) & my food processor for the carrots. I baked in two 9" round cake pans at 350 for about 25-30 mins. For the frosting I used 1 pkg of 8 oz. cream cheese, 3 cups Powdered sugar, 1 stick of softened unsalted butter, 2 t. vanilla, a bit of milk, & approx. 1 t. of cinnamon. You may want to eliminate the milk or I may have over beat the frosting, spread very easily yet you do have to keep refrigerated before serving. A friend told me she liked the frosting. Says it was light & not too rich. I highly recommend this cake! Look over all the reviews & see which tips sound the best to you. Alittle here alittle there. Works for me!!

