My husband had requested a carrot cake for his birthday, and I chose this recipe. Wow, what a keeper! The cake was moist, not oily as some are. I used golden raisins and added more nuts that callled for (I also toasted them first, yum!). I divided the batter into two pans, then split the layers for a total of four, frosting the tops but not the sids. For the frosting, I omitted the 4th cup of powdered sugar and added some homemade orange marmalade, chilled it well and then frosted the cake. The touch of citrus from the marmalade really enhanced the flavor! I topped the cake with more chopped, toasted pecans My father-in-law went nuts when he tasted it, saying, "This is the way a carrot cake should be...it's perfect!"

