So, I gave this recipe to my sister to take to a potluck BBQ celebrating her husband's new job at the boss' home - risky since we had not tried it yet - of course it was a great hit. Or maybe it wasn't a hit, as the other desserts brought by longtime employees wives were overlooked while this one was devoured.....oops. Why is this a top rated recipe? Besides the great taste, it has eye appeal that is not usually associated with what was typically a single layer flat-pan type of cake. It is a wonderful way to re-introduce the common carrot cake taste, so popular in the eighties, in a new way, to new audiences, or even audiences who thought they knew the carrot cake and had made their final opinions. Another thought - perhaps many of these cooks are 'new' - and have not previously had a chance or been responsible for baking, therefore this recipe is truly a discovery. Or, perhaps they are like myself, always searching and testing out 'new' desserts vs well-known desserts, tried and true. The cream cheese icing is a treat, as so many recipes were later adapted sans icing, in keeping with low fat and healthier lifestyles. If you want to have some fun and be on the receiving end of rave reviews, try this one (again)! Enjoy.

