Rating: 4
Three pieces of advice.... 1) why use 1 1/2 cups of flavorless vegetable oil when you can use something I call "nectar of the gods". BUTTER!!! That's right, you can sub all 1 1/2 cups for salted butter or so a partial sub (1/2 cup = 1 stick). 2) add 1/2 cup of crushed pineapple...as Emeril would say, it kicks it up notches unknown to mankind (and please keep the raisins in there) 3) Take the pineapple syrup from the crushed pineapple can and boil it down with some granulated sugar until you have 1 tablespoon or less. Then add it to your frosting for some good Pineapple Cream Cheese Frosting!!!

